SIMPLE: shilly-shally
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shilly-shally
<hw>Shil"ly-shal`ly</hw>, }</mhw> <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[A reduplication
of <ets>shall I</ets>.]</ety> <def>In an irresolute, undecided, or
hesitating manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am somewhat dainty in making a resolution, because when I make
it, I keep it; I don't stand <qex>shill-I-shall-I</qex> then; if I say
't, I'll do 't.</q> <rj><qau>Congreve.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shilly-shally</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Shilly-shally
<hw>Shil"ly-shal`ly</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To hesitate; to act in
an irresolute manner; hence, to occupy one's self with
trifles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shilly-shally</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Shilly-shally
<hw>Shil"ly-shal`ly</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Irresolution; hesitation;
also, occupation with trifles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>She lost not one of her forty-five minutes in picking and
choosing</qex>, -- <qex>no shilly-shally</qex> in Kate.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shiloh</ent>⟦br⟧
